  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key elements:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Proceeds of Crime Act\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n\n3. Compliance Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Business license revocation\n\n5. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Internal Revenue Service (IRS)\n- Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC)\n- Department of Justice (DOJ)\n\n6. Prevention Strategies\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Staff training\n- Enhanced financial transparency\n\n7. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Extradition agreements\n- Joint investigations\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
